text.author: Melissa Lucy
text.title: college day in my life: preparing for finals, study guides, yoga, etc
text.summary1: (human1) An FCGU student tells about how she is studying for her final exam by going over chapters covering the male and female reproductive systems, urinary system and fluid balance, and then goes to exchange a pair of Vans shoes at a DSW shoe store.
text.summary2: (human2) A person makes a day in their life video where she talks about her final exam study schedule for Thanksgiving break, the black perforated Vans she bought from DSW, her encounter at the FGCU library with a girl who said she watches and loves her videos, and her 30 minute process of trying to exchange the Vans at DSW.
text.summary3: (human3) MelissaLucy recounts a typical day in her life in college, which included an early visit to Starbucks to study for her final exam, a shoe exchange at DSW, an encounter with one of her vlog fans at the university library, concluding with her grabbing lunch.
text.summary4: (human4) Melissa Lucy shares a day in her life as a college student at FGCU, in which she laments about the need to review for her human anatomy final exam which takes place in one week, the Tuesday after Thanksgiving Break, and talks about having bought shoes from DSW.
text.summary5: (human5) MelissaLucy describes their day, including time at Starbucks and the library studying for final exams, and discusses the study schedule they created to plan what chapters to study each day, even over Thanksgiving break; they also discuss a trip to DSW to exchange a pair of Vans which don't fit well, and express gratitude to someone who approached them at the library to say hi.
